Defendant Mason T Koehn in court with attorney Adam J. Schleis.  Shawn N Woller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to count #1.  Court finds the defendant guilty of count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.  State makes recommendations.  Attorney Schleis makes statements.  Defendant makes statements. 
The Court Orders the Following:  Count #1

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
1 year jail, without work release.  (Credit -0 days).  
Term of Probation: 2 Years  May be transferred to Milwaukee County 
May have early release from probation after 18 months if agent deems appropriate. 

Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of illegal controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Disclose to any physician in writing your drug history/dependency signed by your physician and provide a copy to your Agent. 
Sign Medical Release for Agent;
Seek employment or school;

Condition Time: 90 days Huber with  NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS -  STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion

COSTS:  $268.00 bail to be applied
DNA Surcharge: $250.00 bail to be applied, rest to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.  
Expunction denied.
